                                         CAPE TOWN - A 21-year-old man from Butterworth has been arrested for allegedly killing his father.  It’s understood the 21-year-old allegedly stabbed his 60-year-old father at their home in Manqulo near Kei Bridge.  The suspect will appear IN the Butterworth Magistrates Court on Wednesday on a murder charge.  The police's Jackson Manatha said, “The incident took place on Friday.” 